      <h3>Quick Answer</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Anabolic resistance is the age-related decline in your muscles' sensitivity to protein — it begins around 40 and accelerates with each decade.</li>
        <li>The core mechanism: the mTOR pathway that triggers muscle protein synthesis requires more leucine per meal to activate after 40.</li>
        <li>The specific threshold: 3.5–4g of leucine per meal — roughly 30–40g of complete protein — is required to reliably trigger MPS in men over 40.</li>
        <li>Anabolic resistance cannot be fully reversed, but it can be overcome by hitting the higher threshold consistently at every meal.</li>
        <li>Three strategies work: more protein per meal, even distribution across the day, and consistent resistance training.</li>
